@Node "1" "Introduction"

                             @{b} Introduction @{ub}

 CedASIF v1 is a Word Processor style Interface to AlphaSpell v5. I wrote
it for my own use because I wonted spell checking IN Ced and not after the
file has been saved. I needed this feature for my Offline mail reader in
which I use Ced as my editor. After closing a mail packet any replies I
have made are compressed and saved in QWK form. So I wrote CedASIF to do
the spell checking before the replies are saved.
 It is a little slow due to having to run AlphaSpell once for every
misspelled word found in the document. The Replace feature is slow also but
I can find no way around it in Ced's ARexx.
@Endnode
@Node "2" "Requierments"

                             @{b} Requirements@{ub}

 Cygnus Ed v3.+ without which you don't need this program.

 ARexx Installed and running.

 AlphaSpell Installed with Environment Variables set to your
Dictionaries.

 This program Installed and setup per instructions.
@Endnode
@Node "3" "Installation"

                             @{b} Installation @{ub}


Copy CedASIF to your Command Path. Defaults to C:

Copy ReqTools.Library and Rexxreqtools.Library to your LIBS:

  Must be done...

 ARexx must be Installed AND Running. I had to talk to Ced by ARexx.

 Load Ced and Install CedASIF into any of your Dos/ARexx Macros. Or
any place you want to call it from.

 Last but not LEAST! Make sure Ced is running on a DEFAULT Public Screen!
For most purposes the Workbench Public Screen is fine. If you run Ced from
a application that Opens a Public Screen be sure that Ced opens on an
Default Public Screen.
 The Best way is to set Ced to use its own Public Screen. This option
is in the Environment Global Settings under Rendering Choices.
@Endnode
@Node "4" "Features'

                               @{b} Features @{ub}

 It will check any file for all misspelled words and then give you an on
screen GUI to correct any found.

 It will replace misspelled words through out your document. This feature
has a String editing prompt with a suggested word replacement, if any was
found. If not an empty String editing prompt will allow you to enter a
corrected spelling of your choice.

 The Window Title Holds Info about what is happening at each step of the
spell correcting.
@Endnode
@Node "5" "Usage"

                                 @{b} Usage @{ub}

 From Ced press the Hot Key you have set CedASIF to. AlphaSpell will
then check the document for errors. If any are found a Requester will
appear on screen with a total of all misspelled words found. The requester
will have Three options for correcting the errors.

 @{" Replace " link "9"}    Replace with correct word in file.
 @{" Save    " link "10"}    Open a second screen to save the Bad words from.
 @{" Quit    " link "11"}    Quit the Spell checker.

 If their are no errors a requester telling you so will appear.
@Endnode
@Node "9" "Replace"

                                @{b} Replace @{ub}

 After pressing Replace from the main Prompt AlphaSpell will try to Guess
the correct spelling for the misspelled word. If a suggested correct
spelling is found you will be presented with a requester with a string
editing prompt on it. One of the suggested correct spellings will be in this
string gadget. The Replace requester will have a suggest button that will
put the next suggested spelling in the string gadget. If no suggested
correct spellings were found you will be presented with an empty string
gadget for hand correcting the spelling.

 Pressing the Replace Button Will correct the word in the entire file by
writing the word in the string gadget in place of the misspelled word. As I
have said before this is slow but it is effective. When the word has been
corrected the next incorrect word will then come up in this requester.

 The Learn button will open a new requester allowing you to add the
word to your User Dictionary.

 The Next Button will SKIP this word and go to the Next incorrectly spelled
word.

 Quit will end your spell checking.  
@Endnode
@Node "10" "Save"

                      @{b} Save for Editing User file @{ub}

 Save will open a second screen on the Ced screen and load the misspelled
words file into it. This option is here so you can edit the word list and
add the GOOD words to your User dictionary.
 This is faster than using the Learn button if you have a large amount
of words to be added to the User Dictionary.

 ~ Note ~ Using this feature ends the spell checking!

@Endnode
@Node "11" "Quit"

                          @{b} Quit Spell Checking @{ub}

 This button ends spell checking whenever it is used.
@Endnode
