@Node "7" "Drawbacks"

                               @{b} Drawbacks@{ub} 

 Most of the drawbacks to using this program are caused by the way
Cygnus Ed does its Replace thru ARexx.

 Due to Cygnus Ed's ARexx, if you need a word capitalized and the
replace word is not, you will have to edit the word in the string gadget.

 If you have puncuation before a word such as this "yes" AlphaSpell
will say the word is misspelled. Also Ced will not Replace any words
that have this problem. I don't know why this is but Replace will not do
it from ARexx.

 Due to having to use ARexx to speak to Ced you can not check any file
larger than 64k. This is built into ARexx for some reason. Left over
from its IBM days I suspect.

 The unregistered version of CedASIF has a Title Prompt at the beginning and
the end of usage. Their is also a short PAUSE delay after these prompts.

 This version uses the Long Guess feature of AlphaSpell. The registered
version has a Preference editor for use of the " n " Option of AlphaSpell.
@Endnode
@Node "8" "Registering"

                         @{b} Registering CedASIF @{ub}

 This program is shareware. If you use it for longer than 30 days you must
register it with the author.

                       @{b} Why should you Register? @{ub}

 The registered version of CedASIF has NO Title Delay and will accept all
options that AlphaSpell supports for spell checking.

 It has a Preference Editor for setting the " n " option of AlphaSpell.
You can also set other Dictionaries for Checking and Learning instead
of the default AlphaSpell environment settings.

 All registered users receive all future updates without paying anything
again ever.

